OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Laizer D. Kornwasser  Director, Bostwick Laboratories, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships46--
Background

		Mr. Laizer D. Kornwasser served as an Executive Vice President and Company Group Chairman of Valeant Pharmaceuticals International, Inc. from February 1, 2013 to July 2015. Mr. Kornwasser served as the Senior Vice President of Consumer Solutions and Retail Markets at Medco Health Solutions, Inc. since July 2011 and also served as its Senior Vice President of Retail Mail & Diabetes Markets since October 2010. He served as Senior Vice President of Channel & Generic Strategy ... at MedcoHealth Solutions Inc. since August 2006 and the President of Liberty Medical since October 2007. He oversaw MedcoHealth's mail and retail channels and generic strategy. He was responsible for developing and executing generic strategies and optimizing channel distribution to significantly reduce client and member pharmacy costs. Mr. Kornwasser joined MedcoHealth in August 2003, initially as its Vice President of Business Development and then served as a Senior Vice President of Business Development and Retail Networks. He founded Edgewood Consulting LLC and served as its Managing Partner. He held positions at Merrill Lynch and Coopers & Lybrand and served as its Associate Professor of Yeshiva University. He has been a Director of Bostwick Laboratories Inc. since February 2008. He serves as a Director of the National Bank of California. He served as a Director of Everyday Health, Inc. since July 23, 2015 until December 5, 2016. Mr. Kornwasser holds a B.S. in Accounting from Yeshiva University in 1992 and a Master in Business Administration from Harvard Business School in 1996.Read Full Background




