						He was the former Senior Executive VP of Medco Health Solutions, reporting directly to the CEO, David Snow. He designed and ran their entire mail-order / specialty pharma business. Medco was found to have committed fraud in several lawsuits and admitted itself, including Rx fraud, Changing Diagnoses to obtain Rx's, faking doctor approvals, Medicare Fraud, Channel Stuffing, etc. The works. It's all public information.

Then ExpressScripts buys Medco and he is fired. Then he re-appears at Valeant, reporting directly to CEO Pearson until the brand new and mysterious title "Company Group Chairman"? His compensation is tied directly to skyrocketing sales, if sales grew by over 30% a year he was to get nearly 300,000 shares a year! That's like $60M/year he was making. Insane. From the day he started to when he mysteriously disappeared when questions started being asked about Valeant's accounting and sales, the share price rocketed from $60 to $260. That made Pearson a billionaire, and Laizer made tens of millions, perhaps a hundred million plus dollars :O Wow.

What's even more strange is he was hired January 2nd, 2013, which was the exact date Philidor was first incorporated.

Hrm.. what do you guys think? Looks like Andrew Left's style of writing too. Pretty damning stuff.

pdfsr dot com/pdf/the-missing-piece

Did Laizer drive Ferrari's and the like at Philidor? That's one rich 40-year old exec.
						 





